cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR 

The paper deals with Visual Question Answering (VQA) models and their robustness to linguistic variations in questions. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. The paper also proposes ways to make models more robust against spurious correlations, which falls under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper uses automated semantic image manipulations and tests for consistency in model predictions, which could also fall under the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
